view.name: LinkNYC Locations
view.description: LinkNYC is replacing the Cityâ€™s outdated public telephones with a network of kiosks that provide free high-speed Wi-Fi, nationwide calling, a dedicated 911 button, charging ports for mobile devices, and access to selected websites. This dataset lists locations where a LinkNYC kiosk has been installed, including sites that have replaced public pay telephones (PPT) and new sites that have been reviewed by community and elected officials.  The Project Status field indicates whether the Link is already active or is still in the process of being connected to electric power and telecommunications fiber.

columns.name: Borough
columns.description: The New York City borough where the hotspots are located.

columns.name: Community Board
columns.description: Appointed advisory groups from a variety of districts throughout NYC's five boroughs.  They deal with issues such as zoning, land usage, and any other matter related to the quality of life of their residents.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: Points that fall North or South of the Equator, expressed in degrees.

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: Points that fall East or West of the Prime Meridian, expressed in degrees.

columns.name: Project Status
columns.description: The phase in which the activation of the kiosk is in after it is installed.

top.item: Link Installed; Connecting Power and Fiber

columns.name: Smallest PPT
columns.description: The Public Pay Telephone unique identification number.

columns.name: Street Address
columns.description: The address of the building the kiosk is located closest to.

columns.name: Link Site ID
columns.description: The location ID of each LinkNYC Kiosk in the format: Borough-Community Board-CB Link ID (i.e. mn-03-123265)

columns.name: Link Smoke Tested and Activated (A)
columns.description: The date in which the construction of a Kiosk was Activated.

columns.name: Link Installation (A)
columns.description: This shows if the kiosk is installed or not.  This is the first stage of the activation process.

columns.name: Neighborhood Tabulation Area (NTA)
columns.description: Neighborhood identifiers to differentiate NYC's five boroughs

columns.name: Location
columns.description: The exact latitude and longitude of each Kiosk.
